    • Method Detail

      • testConsoleQuit

        public void testConsoleQuit()
        Tests the quit command of the interactive console. Asserts that:
        • the program can be terminated by running the command quit
        • the program is not terminated by System.exit(x) with x>0
        • the program does not output anything when being terminated through quit

      • testNoArgs

        public void testNoArgs()
        Tests the program without a command line parameter. Asserts that:
        • the program can be terminated by running the command quit
        • the program is not terminated by System.exit(x) with x>0
        • the program does not output anything when being terminated through quit

      • testWrongArgs

        public void testWrongArgs()
        Tests the program with a bad command line parameter. Asserts that:
        • the program terminates
        • if System.exit(x) is called, x>0
        • an error message is printed

      • simpleInsertTest

        public void simpleInsertTest()
        Tests the insert command. Does not check whether insertions were executed correctly. Asserts that:
        • Assertion works without error messages or exceptions.

      • insertSearchTest

        public void insertSearchTest()
        Uses the insert command to insert and values and search to retrieve them afterwards. Asserts that:
        • search outputs inserted elements consistently
        • insert rewrites elements of existing keys

      • insertSearchTestComplexNames

        public void insertSearchTestComplexNames()
        Uses the insert command to insert "complex" (City names can have spaces) values and search to retrieve them afterwards. Asserts that:
        • search outputs inserted elements consistently

      • searchNull

        public void searchNull()
        Tests the search command for non existent elements. Asserts that:
        • search's output format is correct for non existent elements.

      • searchOnEmptyTree

        public void searchOnEmptyTree()
        Tests the search command on an empty tree. Asserts that:
        • search's output format is correct for the non existent element on an empty tree.
        • the above is true for all valid traverse type arguments.

      • emptyInfoTest

        public void emptyInfoTest()
        Runs the info command on an empty tree. Asserts that:
        • there is no output
        • the above is true for all valid traverse type arguments.

      • preOrderTest

        public void preOrderTest()
        Runs the info command on different filled trees initialised with pre-order traversal. Asserts that:
        • elements are printed in the correct syntax and order.

      • inOrderTest

        public void inOrderTest()
        Runs the info command on different filled trees initialised with in-order traversal. Asserts that:
        • elements are printed in the correct syntax and order.
        • the above is as well true if the program hast been started without a command line argument.

      • levelOrderTest

        public void levelOrderTest()
